Four people died and fifteen others sustained various injuries in a collision between a car and a taxi along the R544 approximately five kilometres before Verena in Mpumalanga, on Monday. On arrival, paramedics found the mangled wrecks. ER24 Spokesperson Werner Vermaak said, “Two people were found dead inside the light motor vehicle. Another two people were found dead inside the taxi”. He added, “Fifteen occupants in the taxi sustained moderate injuries. Majority of the occupants were trapped and had to be freed by local rescue services”. All patients were transported to nearby hospitals in the area for further treatment. The exact circumstances surrounding the collision is not yet known. -TNA Reporter